cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI. 

This paper deals with the task of surgical tool localization in endoscopic videos, which involves computer vision and robotics. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.RO (Robotics and Control) are the most likely categories. The paper proposes a deep learning architecture that is trained with weak supervision, which involves techniques from machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) also likely categories. Finally, the paper uses a large public dataset, which involves multimedia processing, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category as well.
